quran[47]{c,v,t}:
  26,181,Give back full measure and do not be of those who cause loss
  26,182,And weigh with a balance that is straight (correct)
  26,183,"and do not give less to people, the things due to them, and do not cause disturbance in the earth being corrupt"
  26,184,and fear Him Who created you and the ancient generations
  26,185,"They said, \"You are only one of the bewitched"
  26,186,"and you are nothing but a man like us, and our guess about you is that you are of those who lie"
  26,187,Then make pieces from the sky to fall on us if you are of the truthful ones
  26,188,"He said, \"My Lord knows best about what you do"
  26,189,"So they denied him therefore the punishment of the over shadowing cloud seized them, it was certainly a punishment of a great day"
  26,190,"There is certainly a sign in that, but the majority of them does not believe"
  26,191,"And your Lord, He is certainly the Mighty, the Merciful"
  26,192,And the (Quran) has certainly been sent down by the Lord of the worlds
  26,193,the trustworthy spirit came down with it
  26,194,on your heart that you may be (one) of the warners
  26,195,in plain Arabic language
  26,196,and it is (mentioned) in ancient scriptures (too)
  26,197,Is it not a sign for them that the learned (men among) the children of Israel know it
  26,198,And had We sent it down on any of the foreigners
  26,199,"and had he recited it to them, they would not have believed in it"
  26,200,Thus did We cause it to enter into the hearts of the criminals
  26,201,(that) they should not believe in it till they see the painful punishment
  26,202,which will come upon them suddenly while they are not conscious
  26,203,"then they will say, \"Shall we be given time (for amendment)"
  26,204,What ! do they still seek to hasten on Our punishment
  26,205,Then do you see? If We make them enjoy for years
  26,206,then there comes to them that which they were promised
  26,207,"(at that time), that which they were made to enjoy will not be of any use to them"
  26,208,And We did not destroy any town but it had its warners
  26,209,"(for) reminding, and We are not unjust"
  26,210,And the devils have not come down with the (Quran)
  26,211,and it neither suits them nor are they capable (of doing it)
  26,212,(on the contrary) they have been removed far away (even) from hearing (it)
  26,213,"So do not pray to another (presumed) god with God, lest you be of those who are punished"
  26,214,And warn your family (consisting) of close relatives
  26,215,And lower your wing for him who follows you from among the believers
  26,216,"And if they disobey you then say, \"I am certainly free of that which you do"
  26,217,"And put your trust in the Mighty, the Merciful"
  26,218,Who sees you when you stand
  26,219,and your movements among those who prostrate
  26,220,"He is certainly the Hearing, the Knowing"
  26,221,Should I inform you (of those) on whom the devils come down
  26,222,"They come down on every liar, sinner"
  26,223,they deliver hearsay and most of them are liars
  26,224,"And the poets, those in error follow them"
  26,225,Do you not see that they wander distracted in every valley
  26,226,and that they say that which they do not practice
  26,227,"except those who believe and do righteous works and remember God much, and defend themselves after the in-justice that is done to them? And those who are unjust will know, to which place of turning back they will turn back"